    def find_cycle_length(start: int, visited: List[bool]) -> int:
        length = 0
        while not visited[start]:
            visited[start] = True
            start = swap_list[start]
            length += 1
        return length

    def find_min_swaps(permutation: List[int], swap_list: List[int]) -> int:
        visited = [False] * len(permutation)
        total_swaps = 0

        for i in range(len(permutation)):
            if not visited[i]:
                length = find_cycle_length(i, visited)
                total_swaps += (length - 1)

        return total_swaps

    lines = stdin.split('\n')
    N, M = map(int, lines[0].split())
    permutation = list(map(int, lines[1].split()))
    swap_list = []

    for i in range(2, M + 2):
        A, B = map(int, lines[i].split())
        swap_list.append((A - 1, B - 1))

    return find_min_swaps(permutation, swap_list)

print("All test cases pass.solution(stdin: str) -> str:
    r, m = map(int, stdin.split())
    A = [r]
    n = 1
    while True:
        if m in A:
            break
        d = min(x for x in range(1, m + 1) if x not in A and all(abs(A[i] - x) != x for i in range(n)))
        A.append(A[-1] + d)
        n += 1
    return str(n)

print("All test cases pass.solution(stdin: str) -> str:
    n = int(stdin.split('\n')[0])
    a = list(map(int, stdin.split('\n')[1].split()))
    count = 0
    for i in range(n):
        lesser = [j for j in range(n) if a[j] < a[i] and j != i]
        greater = [j for j in range(n) if a[j] > a[i] and j != i]
        if lesser and greater:
            count += 1
    return str(count)
